# Rust is intentionally NOT a Build-Depends: the CI build installs a
# current toolchain via rustup (the dependency tree needs rustc 1.89;
# not all Debian releases carry that yet). dpkg-buildpackage is run with
# -d to skip the Build-Depends check accordingly. The build runs on
# debian:testing (trixie) because stable's libturbojpeg (2.1.5) is below
# the turbojpeg crate's >= 3.0 requirement.
